ic synthesis route.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_008\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Add a literature-supported prebiotic source for phenylpyruvate or demote this to a speculative convergence branch\",\n        \"Specify decarboxylation conditions and whether mineral surfaces or dry heating are involved\",\n        \"Clarify that this branch is proposed, not experimentally validated end-to-end\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.62\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.62,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.58,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.5,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.75,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.62,\n      \"feedback\": \"Direct abiotic transamination or reductive amination of phenylpyruvate to phenylalanine is chemically conceivable and has some indirect support from broader keto-acid amination chemistry, but it is not the validated prebiotic route for phenylalanine and the network does not supply phenylpyruvate formation. As a standalone pathway it is too incomplete and speculative to score highly.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_009\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Add a prebiotic source of phenylpyruvate and specify catalyst candidates such as pyrite, ZnS, or metal ions if claimed\",\n        \"Treat this as a speculative biochemical/prebiotic side route rather than a core pathway\",\n        \"Provide literature support specific to phenylpyruvate-to-phenylalanine abiotic conversion\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.84\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.84,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.72,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.55,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.88,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.78,\n      \"feedback\": \"This path